# jo4 URL Shortener API

REST API for creating and managing short URLs with analytics.

## Authentication

The API supports two authentication methods:

1. **JWT Token** (for web applications): Include the token in the `Authorization` header
2. **API Key** (for server-to-server): Include your API key in the `X-Jo4-API-Key` header

## Code Examples

### Python

```python
import requests

API_URL = "https://jo4-api.jo4.io/api/v1"
API_KEY = "your-api-key"

headers = {"X-Jo4-API-Key": API_KEY, "Content-Type": "application/json"}

# Create a short URL
response = requests.post(
    f"{API_URL}/protected/urls",
    headers=headers,
    json={
        "longUrl": "https://example.com/very/long/path",
        "shortUrl": "my-custom-alias",  # optional
        "title": "My Link",
        "utmSource": "api"
    }
)
data = response.json()
short_url = data["response"]["fullShortUrl"]
print(f"Created: {short_url}")

# Get URL stats
slug = data["response"]["slug"]
stats = requests.get(
    f"{API_URL}/protected/urls/{slug}/stats",
    headers=headers
).json()
print(f"Total clicks: {stats['response']['totalClicks']}")

# List your URLs
urls = requests.get(
    f"{API_URL}/protected/urls/myurls?page=0&size=10",
    headers=headers
).json()
for url in urls["response"]["content"]:
    print(f"{url['shortUrl']} -> {url['longUrl']}")
```

### Node.js

```javascript
const API_URL = 'https://jo4-api.jo4.io/api/v1';
const API_KEY = 'your-api-key';

const headers = {
  'X-Jo4-API-Key': API_KEY,
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
};

// Create a short URL
async function createShortUrl(longUrl, customAlias) {
  const response = await fetch(`${API_URL}/protected/urls`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify({
      longUrl,
      shortUrl: customAlias,
      title: 'My Link'
    })
  });
  const data = await response.json();
  return data.response;
}

// Get URL stats
async function getStats(slug) {
  const response = await fetch(
    `${API_URL}/protected/urls/${slug}/stats`,
    { headers }
  );
  const data = await response.json();
  return data.response;
}

// List your URLs
async function listUrls(page = 0, size = 10) {
  const response = await fetch(
    `${API_URL}/protected/urls/myurls?page=${page}&size=${size}`,
    { headers }
  );
  const data = await response.json();
  return data.response.content;
}

// Usage
(async () => {
  const url = await createShortUrl('https://example.com/page', 'my-link');
  console.log(`Created: ${url.fullShortUrl}`);

  const stats = await getStats(url.slug);
  console.log(`Clicks: ${stats.totalClicks}`);
})();
```

### cURL

```bash
# Create a short URL
curl -X POST "https://jo4-api.jo4.io/api/v1/protected/urls" \
  -H "X-Jo4-API-Key: your-api-key" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"longUrl": "https://example.com", "title": "My Link"}'

# Get URL stats
curl "https://jo4-api.jo4.io/api/v1/protected/urls/{slug}/stats" \
  -H "X-Jo4-API-Key: your-api-key"

# List your URLs
curl "https://jo4-api.jo4.io/api/v1/protected/urls/myurls?page=0&size=10" \
  -H "X-Jo4-API-Key: your-api-key"

# Delete a URL
curl -X DELETE "https://jo4-api.jo4.io/api/v1/protected/urls/{slug}" \
  -H "X-Jo4-API-Key: your-api-key"
```

## Rate Limits

- API keys: 100 requests/minute (configurable per tier)
- JWT auth: 200 requests/minute

Rate limit headers are included in responses:
- `X-RateLimit-Limit`: Maximum requests per window
- `X-RateLimit-Remaining`: Requests remaining in current window
- `X-RateLimit-Reset`: Unix timestamp when the window resets

## Error Responses

All errors follow this format:
```json
{
  "requestId": "uuid",
  "faults": [{
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "description": "Human readable message"
  }]
}
```

Common error codes: `URL_NOT_FOUND`, `URL_ALREADY_EXISTS`, `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED`, `UNAUTHORIZED`
